<section class="trouble" data-section="trouble">
  <h2>When it breaks</h2>
  <div class="trouble-grid">
    <div class="trouble-item">
      <h4>Build failed</h4>
      <p>Open the failed deployment in Railway and read the build logs. Almost always a missing dependency or a typo in <code>package.json</code>.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="trouble-item">
      <h4>App crashes on boot</h4>
      <p>Make sure your app listens on <code>process.env.PORT</code>. Railway assigns the port — hardcoding <code>3000</code> won't work in production.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="trouble-item">
      <h4>Repo missing in Railway</h4>
      <p>It must live in the <strong>Trivelta Vibe Coders</strong> org, not your personal GitHub account. Move it, or recreate from the template inside the org.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="trouble-help">
    <div>
      <p class="trouble-help-kicker">Still blocked?</p>
      <p>Bring the logs and screenshots to <strong>#engineering-with-ai</strong> for help from the team.</p>
    </div>
    <a
      class="trouble-slack-btn"
      href="https://trivelta.slack.com/archives/C0AH0GPSV24"
      target="_blank"
      rel="noopener noreferrer"
    >Open Slack channel</a>
  </div>
</section>
